I found a workaround following [this stackoverflow answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/47495905/6167850).

Just set your `default-runtime` in Docker to `nvidia`. Do this by adding a first-level key to `/etc/docker/daemon.json`, which is `"default-runtime": "nvidia"`.

After changes, my `/etc/docker/daemon.json` looked like this:
```
{
    "default-runtime": "nvidia",
    "runtimes": {
        "nvidia": {
            "path": "nvidia-container-runtime",
            "runtimeArgs": []
        }
    }
}
```

Then run `sudo service docker restart` (note this will kill any currently-running docker containers)
